nl.esciencecenter.xenon

Enum XenonPropertyDescription.Component

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<XenonPropertyDescription.Component>
      • nl.esciencecenter.xenon.XenonPropertyDescription.Component
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<XenonPropertyDescription.Component>
    Enclosing interface:
    XenonPropertyDescription

    public static enum XenonPropertyDescription.Component
extends java.lang.Enum<XenonPropertyDescription.Component>
    The Component enumeration lists all possible parts of Xenon for which a property can be provided.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CREDENTIALS
      Properties for CREDENTIAL components can be passed to the various newCredential calls in Credentials.
      FILESYSTEM
      Properties for FILESYSTEM components can be passed to Files.newFileSystem(String, String, Credential, Map).
      SCHEDULER
      Properties for SCHEDULER components can be passed to Jobs.newScheduler(String, String, Credential, Map).
      XENON
      Properties for XENON components can be passed to XenonFactory.newXenon(Map).
